Company
About Us
Who we are
History
History
Megger
by Sydney Evershed
1889
Sydney Evershed invents the insulation tester.
1903
“Megger” registered as a trademark
1923
AVO Meter, world’s first multi-meter developed.
1936
James Biddle was an importer of Megger insulation testers and later started manufacturing high voltage test instruments. Based in the beautiful National Park of Valley Forge, Pennsylvania, the high voltage tradition continues as Megger’s major site for cable fault location equipment and transformer test equipment.
1946
First commercial cable location from James Biddle Inc.
1951
Based in Dallas, Texas, the Multi-Amp facility concentrated on relay test and circuit breaker test equipment.
1965
During the summer of this year, the Millionth AVOmeter (The Model 8 Mark 3) was manufactured in Dover. Low-voltage Power Factor tester. First low voltage insulation Power Factor test set
1968
AVO acquires Evershed and Vignoles (Megger)
1976
Progamma launches first portable relay tester.
1984
First micro-processor controlled circuit breaker analyser.
1988
First 3 phase relay tester Freja RTS. Portable DFR analyser. PAX launches portable dielectric frequency response analyser for transformers.
1991
’TBG is a privately owned industrial conglomerate based in Switzerland. Thyssen-Bornemisza Group acquires all companies within the AVO group.
1995
Megger, Biddle and Multi-Amp join together.
1999
AVO International renamed to Megger.
2007
2000 J cable fault locater. First cable fault location device with more than 2000 J
2008
PAX (Sweden), specialist transformer diagnostic instruments, joins Megger group.
2012
SebaKMT Group (Germany), world leaders in cable fault location, testing and diagnostics joins.  Includes the HDW (USA) subsidiary specialist in fault location.
2015
Radeburg (DE) HV Research laboratory opened.
2016
Revolutionary TRAX multi-function sub-station tester.
2018
Innovators in electrical testing of motors and generators.
2019
A world leading authority and supplier of products and services dedicated to the measurement and monitoring of partial discharge on High Voltage installations such as substations.
